cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper proposes a method to reduce the complexity of a Conv2D network without sacrificing its accuracy by identifying and removing redundancies in the weights. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research, where deep learning algorithms are widely used. The proposed method involves constructing a new layer, which falls under the category of neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the theoretical statistical learning perspective, which is related to the field of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the experiments are conducted on popular image datasets, such as CIFAR-10 and ImageNet, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning research, further supporting the likelihood of the paper belonging to cs.CV and cs.LG.
